100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 24, 1925, the world is buzzing with news of the upcoming trial of John Thomas Scopes, set to challenge Tennessee's Butler Act that prohibits teaching evolution in schools. In the UK, Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin faces mounting pressure amid ongoing labor disputes, while the League of Nations continues to grapple with post-World War I tensions in Europe. Meanwhile, in the United States, the holiday season sees a surge in consumer spending, reflecting the Roaring Twenties' economic boom.
